The paper focuses on object detection in videos using a combination of convolutional neural networks and long short term memory layers. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes an efficient Bottleneck-LSTM layer, which could be considered a contribution to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with video processing (cs.MM) and optimization of computational cost (cs.NE).
